Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation:

**1. Passing a simple string parameter via query string:**

```csharp
// ProductListPage.xaml.cs or ViewModel
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

**2. Passing the full object via a dictionary:**

```csharp
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), navParams);
}
```

**Receiving both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
        {
            ProductId = idObj.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
            _ = LoadProductAsync(ProductId);
        }

        // Approach 2: full object passed via dictionary
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var productObj) && productObj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }

    private async Task LoadProductAsync(string id)
    {
        Product = await _productService.GetByIdAsync(id);
    }
}
```

**Wire it up — register the route and bind the ViewModel:**

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));

// MauiProgram.cs (DI registration)
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

```xml
<!-- ProductDetailsPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel" ...>
    <!-- BindingContext set via DI constructor injection -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string | Dictionary |
|---|---|---|
| Data type | strings only | any object |
| Appears in URI | yes | no |
| Deep-link friendly | ✅ | ❌ |
| Use when | simple IDs, deep links | complex/large objects |

Both arrive in the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` method — the dictionary approach just preserves the original type so you can cast directly instead of deserializing.
